<section>
  <title><literal>Subsumption</literal></title>
  <para> Represents the fact that one sense from one lexicographic resource is semantically wholly
    contained inside another sense from another lexicographic resource.</para>
  <para>
    Participants:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
    <listitem>
      <para>the broader <literal>Sense</literal> (exactly one) </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>the narrower <literal>Sense</literal> (exactly one)</para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <para>The two senses must not be within the <literal>LexicographicResource</literal>.</para>
</section>
